text: San Pablo City, Laguna is a 1st class Component city in Laguna province, also known as the "City of the Seven Lakes" and one of the oldest cities in the Philippines since 1940s. It is the largest city of Laguna before Calamba City the regional center of Calabarzon. ==Reference== Category:Cities in the Philippines Category:Laguna (province)
title: San Pablo, Laguna
